sec.p:
The working group agreed with the classification of CNVs recommended by the American College of Medical Genetics (ACMG):
pathogenic;
uncertain clinical significance: likely pathogenic;
uncertain clinical significance;
uncertain clinical significance: likely benign;
benign.34

list-item.p:
Variants characterised as:
‘uncertain clinical significance: likely benign’ or;
‘benign’ should not be reported.
